text: Goes, Zeelandic: Goes or Hoes, is a municipality and town on the former island of Zuid-Beveland, Province of Zeeland, the Netherlands. About 37,000 people were living in the municipality in 2017. About 27,000 people were living in the town in 2010. There are a lot of villages is the municipality like: Kattendijke, Kloetinge, 's-Heer Hendrikskinderen, 's-Heer Arendskerke/Eindewege, Wilhelminadorp and Wolphaartsdijk/Oud-Sabbinge. There are also some districts like Blauwewijk, Goese Sas, Monnikendijk and Roodewijk Goes has had city rights since 1405. ==References== == Other websites == * Category:Cities in Zeeland Category:Municipalities of Zeeland
